---
title: Array field
---
The `array` field is used to create "Add one more" scenarios where you need _one or multiple_ instances of a specific field schema.

You can only pass a single field to the `array` field â€” but this field can be an [object](/docs/fields/object) field to create complex structures.

The `label` for the `array` field can optionally be defined in the second parameter, as an options object. It's also useful to define the `itemLabel` for each instance of the array, to give it a more meaningful label than the default `Item 1`, `Item 2` etc.

## Example usage

### Simple

```typescript
tags: fields.array(
  fields.text({ label: 'Tag' }),
  // Labelling options
  {
    label: 'Tag',
    itemLabel: props => props.value
  }
)
```

### Complex

```typescript
complexArray: fields.array(
  fields.object({
    name: fields.text({ label: 'Name' }),
    age: fields.integer({ label: 'Age' }),
    projects: fields.array(
      fields.relationship({
        label: 'Projects',
        collection: 'projects',
        validation: {
          isRequired: true,
        },
      }),
      {
        label: 'Projects',
        itemLabel: (props) => props.value ?? 'Select a project',
      }
    ),
  }),
  // Labelling options
  {
    label: 'Complex Array',
    itemLabel: (props) => props.fields.name.value,
  }
),
```

